title: Google pays Apple billions a year to use its search engine. Now executives must testify.
description: Lucrative, closed-door dealings between Apple and Google are under scrutiny at an antitrust trial in Washington, as senior Apple executives take the stand.

title: Ex-workers allege TikTok’s owner retaliated after racism complaints
description: Two Black ex-employees allege in a new Equal Employment Opportunity Commission charge that their managers retaliated against them after they complained about racism.

title: Return to the office? These workers quit instead.
description: Companies are increasingly cracking down on remote work, spurring employee pushback and resignations.
